metadata.description: The Swing, also known as The Happy Accidents of the Swing (French: Les Hasards heureux de l'escarpolette, original title), is an 18th-century oil painting by Jean-Honor√© Fragonard in the Wallace Collection in London. It is considered one of the masterpieces of the Rococo period and is Fragonard's best-known work.
